thecrag Facebook Publishing

<p>Acents logged in thecrag.com may also be logged in your Facebook Wall. This service must be setup from thecrag.com and is selectable on a per ascent basis as you log an ascent.</p>

<p>To setup this service you must:</p>
<ul>
  <li><p>Log in to your thecrag.com account;</p></li>
  <li><p>Click on th 'My Account' tab;</p></li>
  <li><p>Select Action > Setup Facebook Publishing; and</p></li>
  <li><p>Follow prompts.</p></li>
</ul>

<p>Note you will be asked by Facebook to grant the application (known as 'thecrag.com Publishing' on Facebook) permissions to publish on your wall. If you don't give the application permission then the service cannot be activated on your account.</p>


<h2>Logging Ascents</h2>
<p>Once setup, every time you log an ascent you will have the option post the ascent on your Facebook Wall. The ascent must have been made in the last 10 days.</p>

<p>The post for each ascent will look something like this:</p>

<p><img src="/static/cids/images/fb-logging-example-1.1.0.gif" /></p>

<p>Posts will also have a link to a climb, so your friends will be able to see what you have climbed.</p>


<h2>Privacy Policy</h2>

<p>thecrag.com is committed to respecting the privacy of its customers. The following policy discusses how personal information received by thecrag.com will be dealt with in respect to the 'thecrag.com Publishing' application on Facebook.</p>

<p>The application seeks permission to publish entries you make on thecrag.com on your Facebook Wall account. We will not publish unless you explicity opt in for each entry you make at thecrag.com.</p>

<p>The service collects your account number and account name so that thecrag.com may interface to your Facebook account. This is stored securily in our system. This information is not passed on to any third party unless requested by the user, required to by law or as the direct fulfilment of the offered service.</p>

<p>We may use this information to help identify you for other services offered by thecrag.com on Facebook.</p>

<p>You may disable the service either at thecrag.com by using the 'Setup Facebook Pubishing' button on your Account Portal page or directly in Facebook by deselecting the application permissions.</p>


<h2>Support</h2>

<p>You may contact thecrag.com support email (&#115;&#117;&#112;&#112;&#111;&#114;&#116; &#64;  thecrag.com) if you require any support for this service.</p>
